description:
Non-material amendment of planning permission P082407 dated 23 July 2009 which granted 'Demolition of all existing buildings (2768 sq.m GIA) and erection of a six (plus mezzanine) storey building, with partial basement, comprising: 1459 sq.m of flexible Use Classes B1  / B8 floorspace at ground floor, and up to 1396 sq.m of class B1 floorspace on partial mezzanine(s), and 400 student bedrooms (65 x 6 bed flats and 10 x studios) on upper floors; together with five disabled car parking spaces, 235 cycle parking spaces service yard, landscaping and other associated works'. The non-material amendments sought include:
a)	insertion of a condition listing the approved drawing and documents;
b)	changes to the layout of the student accommodation without increasing the overall number of bedspaces (400) to improve mobility impaired access and provide complying fire escape 
c)	consolidation of a single student entrance, reduction in size of B1/B8 access cores and provision of level access;
d)	revised layout and redistribution of accessible car parking spaces, motorcycle parking spaces and cycle store locations;
e)	infilling under cantilevered elements located at the rear of the building
